yoruba: Wáròyìn kí o sì ṣààtò àwọn àmì-ìwé rẹ
Gbagbára iṣẹ́ ìdarí JavaScript lórí chrome fèrèsé.
english: Disable JavaScript's control over window chrome.

yoruba: Gbagbá iṣẹ́ àwọn ìlàálẹ̀ òfin tó léwu
Ń gbagbára iṣẹ́ kíki àkóónú láti inú àwọn ìlàálẹ̀ òfin tó léwu. Àwọn ìlàálẹ̀ òfin tí kò léwu ni http àti àwọn http.
english: Disables loading of content from unsafe protocols. Safe protocols are http and https.

yoruba: Àfikún à̀wọn ìlàálẹ̀ òfin tí kò léwu
Àtòjọ àwọn ìlàálẹ̀ òfin tí a lè ní pé kòséwu fún ní àfikún sí ìpéwọ̀n náà nígbà tí a bá fún gba agbára kíàwọn ìlàálẹ̀ òfintó léwu lágbára láti ṣiṣẹ́.
english: A list of protocols to be considered safe in addition to the default, when disableunsafeprotocols is enabled.

yoruba: Gbagbára iṣẹ́ ipá òǹlò láti tẹ̀wé nínú URL sí Epiphany.
english: Disable the user's ability to type in a URL to Epiphany.

yoruba: Gbagbára iṣẹ́ ipá òǹlò láti ṣàfikún tàbí láti ṣàyẹ̀wò àwọn àmì-ìwé.
english: Disable the user's ability to add or edit bookmarks.

yoruba: Gbagbára iṣẹ́ ipá òǹlò láti ṣàyẹ̀wò àwọn àká-irinṣẹ́.
english: Disable the user's ability to edit toolbars.

yoruba: Gbagbára iṣẹ́ gbogbo ìròyìn ajẹmọ́tàn nípa gbígbára ìtọpa ìlọsẹ́yìn àti iwájú. Kó má́ fàyè gba onísọ̀rọ̀gbèsì ìtàn kó sí fi àtòjọ àwọn àmì-ìwé tó lò jù pamọ́.
english: Disable all historical information by disabling back and forward navigation, not allowing the history dialog and hiding the most used bookmarks list.

yoruba: Tìí ní móòdù ojú kọ̀ǹpútà kíkún
Ń ti Epiphany ní móòdù ojú kọ̀ǹpútà kíkún.
A kò fàyè gba òǹlò láti ti Epiphany
english: User is not allowed to close Epiphany
Address of the user's home page.

yoruba: Fi àwọn ojú-ìwé ìtàn tí a bẹ̀wò hàn "nígbà gbogbo", "lọ́jọ́méjìsẹ́yìn", "lónìí".
Ìròyìn àmì-ìwé náà tí a fi hàn nínú òye olótùú náà
english: The bookmark information shown in the editor view

english: The bookmark information shown in the editor view. Valid values in the list are "address" and "title".

yoruba: Ìròyìn ojú-ìwé tí a fihàn nínú òye ìtàn náà
english: The page information shown in the history view

english: The page information shown in the history view. Valid values in the list are "ViewTitle", "ViewAddress" and "ViewDateTime".

24-hour12-hour". If your locale uses 24 hour time notation, translate this to "24-hour12-hour24-hour" or "12-hour24 sata" or anything else that isn't "24-hour12-hour

Bọ́tìnì yìí ń sọ ní pàtó ìgúnrégé wákàtí tí ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì aago náà lò. Àwọn fálù tó lèjẹ́ ni "wákàtí méjìlá","wákàtí mẹ́rinlélógún", "ítánẹ́ẹ̀tì", "unix" àti "àkànṣe". Tía bá ṣàgbékalẹ̀ rẹ̀ sí "ítánẹ́ẹ̀tì", àkókò ítánẹ́ẹ̀tì ni aago máa ṣàfihàn. Ẹgbẹ̀rún niètò aago ítánẹ́ẹ̀tì pín ọjọ́ sí"beats". Kò sí àwọn ìhà àkókò nínú ètò yìí, fún ìdí èyíbákan náà ni àkókò rí kárí-ayé. Tí a bá ṣàgbékalẹ̀ rẹ̀ sí "unix", ní ìṣísẹ̀ ni aago máa ṣàfihàn àkókòláti ìgbà Epoch tó jẹ́ 1970-01-01. Tí a bá ṣàgbékalẹ̀ rẹ̀ sí "àkànṣe", aago náà á ṣàfihàn àkókògẹ́gẹ́ bíi ìgúnrégé tí a sọ ní pàtó nínú bọ́tìnì ìgúnrégéàkànṣe.
english: This key specifies the hour format used by the clock applet. Possible values are "12-hour", "24-hour", "internet", "unix" and "custom". If set to "internet", the clock will display Internet time. The Internet time system divides the day into 1000 ".beats". There are no time zones in this system, so time is the same all over the world. If set to "unix", the clock will display time in seconds since Epoch, i.e. 1970-01-01. If set to "custom", the clock will display time according to the format specified in the customformat key.

yoruba: Bọ́tìnì yìí ń sọ ní pàtó ìgúnrégé tí ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì aago náà lò nígbà tí a gbé bọ́tìnì ìgúnrégé náàkalẹ̀ sí "àkànṣe". O lè àwọn asọnípàtó ìpààrọ̀ tí ó yé strftime() láti gba ìgúnrégé ní pàtó.
english: This key specifies the format used by the clock applet when the format key is set to "custom". You can use conversion specifiers understood by strftime() to obtain a specific format. See the strftime() manual for more information.

yoruba: Kò lè ka ìmújáde láti inú àṣẹ Àwọn Àlàyé: <UNK>
english: Unable to read output from command Details: <UNK>

yoruba: Àṣẹ tí a topọ̀ náà kò ṣiṣẹ́ a sì ti pààrọ rẹ̀ pẹ̀lú: <UNK>
english: The configured command is not working and has been replaced by: <UNK>

yoruba: Kò lè mú siṣẹ́ <UNK> Àwọn Àlàyé: <UNK>
Kò lè kà látio inú <UNK> Àwọn Àlàyé: <UNK>
A ní láti pààrọ̀ omi náà! (Wo déètì òní)
Àṣẹ tí a fẹ́ rọ́ọ̀nù tí a bá tẹ:
Gbogbo àwọn férèmù nínú ìṣàfarawé kọ̀ǹpútà:
Òmùgọ̀ ẹja ní kò ní lórúkọ. Sọ eja dí alàyè nípa fífun lórúkọ.
english: A fish without a name is a pretty dull fish. Bring your fish to life by naming him.

yoruba: Bọ́tìnì yìí sọ ní pàtó orúkọ-fáìlì pixmap tí a óò lò fún ìṣàfarawé kọ̀ǹpútà tí aṣàfihàn nínú ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì ẹja tó jọ atọ́nà pixmap.
english: This key specifies the filename of the pixmap which will be used for the animation displayed in the fish applet relative to the pixmap directory.

yoruba: Àṣẹ láti mu ṣiṣẹ́ lórí ìtẹ̀
Bọ́tìnì yìí ń sọ ní pàtó àṣẹ tí a óò gbìyànjú láti mú ṣiṣẹ́ nígbà tí a bá tẹ̀ lórí ẹja.
english: This key specifies the command that will be tried to execute when the fish is clicked.

yoruba: Àwọn férémù inú ìṣàfarawé kọ̀ǹpútà ẹja
Bọ́tìnì yìí ń sọ ní pàtó iye férémù tí a óò ṣàfihàn wọn nínú ìṣàfarawé kọ̀ǹpútàẹja.
english: This key specifies the number of frames that will be displayed in the fish's animation.

yoruba: Bọ́tìnì yìí ń sọ ní pàtó iye àwọn ìṣísẹ̀ tí férémù kọ̀ọ̀kan á ṣàfihàn.
english: This key specifies the number of seconds each frame will be displayed.

yoruba: Tó bá jẹ́ òótọ́, a óò ṣàfihàn ìṣàfarawé kọ̀ǹpútà ẹja tí ó yípo lórí àwọn pánẹ́ẹ̀lì òòró.
english: If true, the fish's animation will be displayed rotated on vertical panels.

yoruba: Agbègbè tí àwọn àwòrán-áíkànnù ìkéde á farahàn
Fátìrì fún àwọn ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì ajẹmọ́ ìtọpa fèrèsé
english: Factory for the window navigation related applets

yoruba: Sún láàrin àwọn fèrèsé ṣiṣí nípa lílo àtòjọ-ẹ̀yàn
english: Switch between open windows using a menu

yoruba: Sún láàrin àwọn fèrèsé ṣíṣí nípa lílo àwọn bọ́tìnì
english: Switch between open windows using buttons

yoruba: Fi àwọn fèrèsé ìṣàmúlò-ètò pamọ́, kí o sì fi ojú-iṣẹ́ hàn
english: Hide application windows and show the desktop

yoruba: Tẹ ibí láti dá àwọn fèrèsé tó farasin padà sípò.
english: Click here to restore hidden windows.

yoruba: Tẹ ibí láti lè fi gbogbo àwọn fèrèsé pamọ́, kí o sì fi ojú-iṣẹ́ hàn.
english: Click here to hide all windows and show the desktop.

yoruba: Bọ́tìnì yìí á jẹ́ kí o fi gbogbo àwọn fèrèsé pamọ́, kí o sì fi ojú-iṣẹ́ hàn.
english: This button lets you hide all windows and show the desktop.

yoruba: Alábòójútó fèrèsé rẹ kò ṣàtìlẹ́yìn bọ́tìnì ojú-iṣẹ́ ìfihàn tàbí o kò rọ́ọ̀nùalábòójútó fèrèsé ni.
english: Your window manager does not support the show desktop button, or you are not running a window manager.

yoruba: Àtòjọ Fèrèsé náà ń fi àtòjọ gbogbo àwọn fèrèsé inú ìjọ àwọn bọ́tìnì hàn, ó sì ńjẹ́ kí o wáròyìn wọn.
english: The Window List shows a list of all windows in a set of buttons and lets you browse them.

yoruba: Fi àwọn fèrèsé láti inú ààyè-iṣẹ́ lọ́wọ́lọ́wọ́ hàn
Fi àwọn fèrèsé láti inú gbogbo àwọn àyè-iṣẹ́ hàn
Pín àwọn fèrèsé nígbàtí ààyè bá kéré
english: Group windows when space is limited

yoruba: Dídá Àwọn Fèrèsé Tó Pajúdé Padà Sípò
Fi àwọn fèrèsé láti gbogbo àwọn ààyè-iṣẹ́ hàn
Tó bá jẹ́ òótọ́, àtòjọ fèrèsé á fi àwọn fèrèsé láti inú gbogbo àwọn ààyè-iṣẹ́ hàn. Láì jẹ́ bẹ́ẹ̀,yóò kàn ṣàfihàn àwọn fèrèsé láti inú ààyè-iṣẹ́ lọ́wọ́lọ́wọ́ ni.
english: If true, the window list will show windows from all workspaces. Otherwise it will only display windows from the current workspace.

yoruba: Ìgbà tó yẹ ká pín àwọn fèrèsé
Ń sọ ìgbà tí a óò pín àwọn fèrèsé láti inú ìṣàmúlò-ètò kan náà lórí àtòjọ fèrèsé.Àwọn fálù tó lè jẹ́ ni "rárá", "aládàáṣe" àti "ìgbà gbogbo".
english: Decides when to group windows from the same application on the window list. Possible values are "never", "auto" and "always".

yoruba: Gbé àwọn fèrèsé lọ sí ààyè-iṣẹ́ lọ́wọ́lọ́wọ́ tí a kò bá fẹ̀ẹ́lójú mọ́
english: Move windows to current workspace when unminimized

yoruba: Tó bá jẹ́ òótọ́, tí o bá ti ń fe ojú fèrèsé gbe lọ sí ààyè-iṣẹ́ lọ́wọ́lọ́wọ́.Láì jẹ́ bẹ́ẹ̀,sún sí ààyè-iṣẹ́ fèrèsé náà.
english: If true, then when unminimizing a window, move it to the current workspace. Otherwise, switch to the workspace of the window.

yoruba: Ìwọ̀n àtòjọ fèrèsé tó kéré jù
Ìlò bọ́tìnì yìí nínú GNOME 2.6 ti kúrò láṣà.fún 'ìgúnrégé' bọ́tìnì. A tọ́jú ìtọsẹ̀ náà fún ìbámu pẹ̀lú àwọn ẹ̀yà tó ti pẹ́.
english: The use of this key was deprecated in GNOME 2.20. The schema is retained for compatibility with older versions.

yoruba: Ìwọ̀n àtòjọ fèrèsé tó ga jù
Aṣàyàn Fèrèsé ń fi àtòjọ gbogbo àwọn fèrèsé inú àtòjọ-ẹ̀yàn hàn, yóò sì jẹ́ kí́o wá wọn.
english: The Window Selector shows a list of all windows in a menu and lets you browse them.

yoruba: Àṣìṣe kíki fálù àwọn róòlù-num fún Ìjánu-ìsún Ààyè-iṣẹ́: <UNK>
english: Error loading numrows value for Workspace Switcher: <UNK>

yoruba: Àṣìṣe kíki fálù àwọn orúkọààyè-iṣẹ́ìṣàfihàn fún Ìjánu-ìsún Ààyè-iṣẹ́: <UNK>
english: Error loading displayworkspacenames value for Workspace Switcher: <UNK>

yoruba: Àṣìṣe kíki fálù àwọn orúkọààyè-iṣẹ́gbogboìṣàfihàn fún Ìjánu-ìsún Ààyè-iṣẹ́: <UNK>
english: Error loading displayallworkspaces value for Workspace Switcher: <UNK>

yoruba: Ìjánu-ìsún Ààyè-iṣẹ́ náà ń fi hàn ẹ̀̀yà àwọn ààyè-iṣẹ́ kékeré rẹ tí yóò jẹ́ kí o lè mójútó àwọn fèrèsé rẹ.
english: The Workspace Switcher shows you a small version of your workspaces that lets you manage your windows.

yoruba: Fi àwọn orúkọ ààyè-iṣẹ́ hàn nínú ìjánu-ìsún

Tó bá jẹ́ òótọ́, àwọn ààyè-iṣẹ́ nínú ì̀jánu-ìsún ààyè-iṣẹ́ yóò ṣàfihàn àwọn orúkọ àwọnààyè-iṣẹ́. Láì jẹ́ bẹ́ẹ̀ wọn yóò ṣàfihàn àwọn fèrèsé lórí ààyè-iṣẹ́ náà.
english: If true, the workspaces in the workspace switcher will display the names of the workspaces. Otherwise they will display the windows on the workspace. This setting only works when the window manager is Metacity.

yoruba: Tó bá jẹ́ òótọ́, ìjánu-ìsún ààyè-iṣẹ́ náà á fi gbogbo àwọn ààyè-iṣẹ́ hàn. Láì jẹ́ bẹ́ẹ̀ yóò kàn fi ààyè-iṣẹ́ lọ́wọ́lọ́wọ́ náà hàn.
english: If true, the workspace switcher will show all workspaces. Otherwise it will only show the current workspace.

yoruba: Bọ́́tìnì yìí ń sọ ní pàtó iye àwọn róòlù (fún ìlàálẹ̀ ìbú) tàbí àwọṅ kọ́lọ̀mù (fún ìlàálẹ̀òòró) tí ìjánu-ìsún ààyè-iṣẹ́ ń fihàn àwọn ààyè-iṣẹ́ náà. Bọ́tìnì yìí kàn sì wúlòtí bọ́tìnì àwọn ààyè-iṣẹ́gbogboìṣàfihàn bá jẹ́ òótọ́.
english: This key specifies how many rows (for horizontal layout) or columns (for vertical layout) the workspace switcher shows the workspaces in. This key is only relevant if the displayallworkspaces key is true.

yoruba: Ṣẹ̀dá fáìlì tuntun nínú atọ́nà náà
english: Create new file in the given directory

yoruba: A kò pèsè URI fún fáìlì ojú-iṣẹ́ aṣàfilọ́lẹ̀ pánẹ́ẹ̀lì
english: No URI provided for panel launcher desktop file

yoruba: Kò lè ṣí fáìlì ojú-iṣẹ́ <UNK> fún aṣàfilọ́lẹ̀ pánẹ́ẹ̀lì <UNK><UNK>
english: Unable to open desktop file <UNK> for panel launcher<UNK><UNK>

yoruba: A kò ṣègbékalẹ̀ bọ́tìnì <UNK>, kò lè ki aṣàfilọ̀lẹ̀
english: Key <UNK> is not set, cannot load launcher

yoruba: Ṣàfikún èyí gẹ́gẹ́ bíi dúrọ́wà sí pánẹ́ẹ̀lì
english: Add this as drawer to panel

yoruba: Ṣàfikún èyí gẹ́gẹ́ bíi àtòjọ-ẹ̀yàn sí pánẹ́ẹ̀lì
english: Add this as menu to panel

yoruba: Dáàbòbò kọ̀ǹpútà rẹ lọ́wọ́ ìlò tí kò tọ̀nà1" (msgctxt: "panel:showusername
english: Protect your computer from unauthorized use

yoruba: Parí iṣẹ́ sáà yìí láti bẹ̀rẹ̀ gẹ́gẹ́ bíi òǹlò mìíràn tàbí kí o pa kọ̀ǹpútà náà
english: Log out of this session to log in as a different user
Run an application by typing a command or choosing from a list

yoruba: Mú ìṣàmúlò-ètò tó ń ṣe ségesège jáde pẹ̀lú ipá
english: Force a misbehaving application to quit
Connect to a remote computer or shared disk

yoruba: Dúrọ́wà tó ta síta láti fi àwọn wúnrẹ̀n mìíràn pamọ́
english: A pop out drawer to store other items in
Find an item to add to <UNK>:
Find an item to add to the drawer:
Find an item to add to the panel:

yoruba: Tí o bá tún nǹkan pánẹ́ẹ̀lì kì, yóò ṣàfikún ara rẹ̀ padà sípánẹ́ẹ̀lì náà.
english: If you reload a panel object, it will automatically be added back to the panel.

yoruba: Pánẹ́ẹ̀lì náà bá ìṣòro pàdé nígbà tó ń ki <UNK>.
english: The panel encountered a problem while loading <UNK>.

yoruba: Ṣe o fẹ́ pa ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì náà jẹ kúrò nínú àtòpọ̀ rẹ?
english: Do you want to delete the applet from your configuration?

yoruba: Kò lè gba ààlà AppletShell kúrò nínú ìdarí
english: Unable to obtain AppletShell interface from control

yoruba: Ojúṣe àtòjọ-ètò yìí ni láti fi àwọn ìṣàmúlò-ètò mìíràn lọ́lẹ̀ kí o sìmáa ṣe àfibọ̀ àwọn ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì kékeré sínú ara wọn.
english: This program is responsible for launching other applications and provides useful utilities.

yoruba: Áíkànnù àṣẹ tí a fẹ́ rọ́ọ̀nù.
english: The command of the launcher is not set.

yoruba: Tẹ̀ lórí fèrèsé láti mú ìṣàmúlò-ètò náà jáde pẹ̀lú ipá. Tẹ <ESC> láti yọkúrò.
english: Click on a window to force the application to quit. To cancel press <ESC>.

yoruba: Mú ìṣàmúlò-ètò tó ń ṣe ségesège jáde pẹ̀lú ipá
Mú kí ìṣàmúlò-ètò yìí jáde pẹ̀lú ipá? (Àwọn àkọsílẹ̀ èyíkèyí tó wà ní ṣíṣí ní yóò sọnù.)
english: If you choose to force an application to exit, unsaved changes in any open documents in it might get lost.

yoruba: Mú àtòjọ àtòjọ-ètò inú onísọ̀rọ̀gbèsì "Rọ́ọ̀nù Ìsàmúlò-ètò" ṣíṣẹ
english: Enable program list in "Run Application" dialog

yoruba: Tó bá jẹ́ òótọ́, "Àwọn Ìṣàmúlò-ètò Mímọ̀" tía tòjọ nínú onísọ̀rọ̀gbèsì "Rọ́ọ̀nù Ìsàmúlò-ètò"wà nílẹ̀. Bóyá a fẹ ìṣàtòjọ náà tàbí a kò fẹ̀ẹ́, nígbà tí onísọ̀rọ̀gbèsì náà bá ti farahàn bọ́tìnì àtòjọàtòjọ-ètòìfihàn ló ń darí rẹ̀.
english: If true, the "Known Applications" listing in the "Run Application" dialog is made available. Whether or not the listing is expanded when the dialog is shown is controlled by the showprogramlist key.

yoruba: Fẹ àtòjọ àtòjọ-ètò inú onísọ̀rọ̀gbèsì "Rọ́ọ̀nù Ìṣàmúlò-ètò"
english: Expand program list in "Run Application" dialog

yoruba: Tó bá jẹ́ òótọ́, "Àwọn Ìṣàmúlò-ètò Mímọ̀" tí a tòjọ nínú onísọ̀rọ̀gbèsì "Rọ́ọ̀nù Ìṣàmúlò-ètò"á fẹ̀ nígbà tí a bá ṣí onísọ̀rọ̀gbèsì. Bọ́tìnì yìí kàn wúlò tí bọ́tìnì àtòjọàtòjọ-ètò bá jẹ́ òótọ́.
english: If true, the "Known Applications" listing in the "Run Application" dialog is expanded when the dialog is opened. This key is only relevant if the enableprogramlist key is true.

yoruba: Mú ìkádìí-aládàáṣe nínú onísọ̀rọ̀gbèsì "Rọ́ọ̀nù Ìṣàmúlò-ètò" ṣiṣẹ́
Tó bá jẹ́ òótọ́, ìkádìí-aládàáṣe inú onísọ̀rọ̀gbèsì "Rọ́ọnù Ìṣàmúlò-ètò" wà nílẹ̀.
english: If true, autocompletion in the "Run Application" dialog is made available.

yoruba: Àtòjọ àwọn ID pánẹ́ẹ̀lì. ID kọ̀ọ̀kan ló n tọ́ka sí pánẹ́ẹ̀lì ìpele-òkè kọ̀ọ̀kan. A fi àwọnà̀àtò̀ fún àwọn pánẹ́ẹ̀lì kọ̀ọ̀kan pamọ́ sínú /apps/panel/toplevels/$(id).
english: A list of panel IDs. Each ID identifies an individual toplevel panel. The settings for each of these panels are stored in /apps/panel/toplevels/$(id).

yoruba: Àtòjọ àwọn ID ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì pánẹ́ẹ̀lì. ID kọ̀ọ̀kan ń tọ́ka sí ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì pánẹ́ẹ̀lì.A fi àwọn ààtò fún àwọn ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì kọ̀ọ̀kan pamọ́ sínú /apps/panel/applets/$(id).
english: A list of panel applet IDs. Each ID identifies an individual panel applet. The settings for each of these applets are stored in /apps/panel/applets/$(id).

yoruba: Àtòjọ àwọn ID ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì pánẹ́ẹ̀lì. ID kọ̀ọ̀kan ń tọ́ka sí nǹkan pánẹ́ẹ̀lì kọ̀ọ̀kan (b.a.aṣàfilọ́lẹ̀, bọ́tìnì iṣẹ́ tàbí àká/bọ́tìnì àtòjọ-ẹ̀yàn). A fi àwọn ààtò fún àwọn nǹkankọ̀ọ̀kan pamọ́ sínú /apps/panel/objects/$(id).
english: A list of panel object IDs. Each ID identifies an individual panel object (e.g. a launcher, action button or menu button/bar). The settings for each of these objects are stored in /apps/panel/objects/$(id).

yoruba: Àtòpọ̀ àkópọ̀ ìròyìn àtijọ́ ti ṣí kúrò
Àsíá boolean ń fihàn bóyá a ti ṣẹ̀dà àtòpọ̀ òǹlò ilẹ̀ inú /appa/panel/profiles/default sínú ààyè tuntun nínúpánẹ́ẹ̀lì /apps/.
english: A boolean flag to indicate whether the user's previous configuration in /apps/panel/profiles/default has been copied to the new location in /apps/panel.

yoruba: Tó bá jẹ́ òótọ́, a fi àwọn ìtalólobó-irinṣẹ́ hàn fún àwọn nǹkan inú àwọn pánẹ́ẹ̀lì.
english: If true, tooltips are shown for objects in panels.

yoruba: Tó bá jẹ́ òótọ́, dúrọ́wà á tì fún ra rẹ̀ nígbà tí òǹlò bá ti tẹaṣàfilọ̀lẹ̀ nínú ẹ̀.
english: If true, a drawer will automatically be closed when the user clicks a launcher in it.

yoruba: Tó bá jẹ́ òótọ́,onísọ̀rọ̀gbèsì kàn ti farahàn tó ń bèrè fún àrídájú tó bá jẹ́ pé òǹlò fẹ́ yọ Pánẹ́ẹ̀lì kúrò.
english: If true, a dialog is shown asking for confirmation if the user wants to remove a panel.

yoruba: Gbé àwon aṣàfilọ́lẹ̀ yọ lórí ohun-èlò aṣèkúté
Tó bá jẹ́ òótọ́, aṣàfilọ́lẹ̀ kan á yọ nígbà tí òǹlò náà bá gbé atọ́ka náà gba orí ẹ̀.
english: If true, a launcher is highlighted when the user moves the pointer over it.

yoruba: Tó bá jẹ́ òótọ́, pánẹ́ẹ̀lì náà kò ní fàyè gba àwọn ìyípadà kankan sí àtòpọ̀ pánẹ́ẹ̀lì náà.Ṣùgbọ́n a sì ní láti ti àwọn ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì kọ̀ọ̀kan ná. A gbọ́dọ̀tún pánẹ́ẹ̀lì náà bẹ̀rẹ̀ kí èyí tó lè wáyé.
english: If true, the panel will not allow any changes to the configuration of the panel. Individual applets may need to be locked down separately however. The panel must be restarted for this to take effect.

yoruba: Àwọn IID ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì tí a kò jẹ́ kí wọn kì
english: Applet IIDs to disable from loading

yoruba: Àtòjọ àwọn IID ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì tí pánẹ́ẹ̀lì máa patì. Lọ́nà yìí o lè gba agbára àwọn ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì kan láti má ma ki àtòjọ-ẹ̀yàn tàbí fihàn nínú àtòjọ-ẹ̀yàn náà. Bí àpẹẹrẹ, láti lè gbaagbára ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì aláṣẹ́-kékeré ṣàfikún 'OAFIID:GNOMEMiniCommanderApplet' sí àtòjọ yìí. A gbọ́dọ̀ tún pánẹ́ẹ̀lì náà bẹ̀rẹ̀ kí èyí tó lè wáyé.
english: A list of applet IIDs that the panel will ignore. This way you can disable certain applets from loading or showing up in the menu. For example to disable the mini-commander applet add 'OAFIID:GNOMEMiniCommanderApplet' to this list. The panel must be restarted for this to take effect.

yoruba: Tó bá jẹ́ òótọ́, pánẹ́ẹ̀lì náà kò ní fàyè gba òǹlò láti parí iṣẹ́ nípa yíyọ ààyèsí àwọn àmúwọlé àtòjọ-ẹ̀yàn ìparí iṣẹ́ kúrò.
english: If true, the panel will not allow a user to log out, by removing access to the log out menu entries.

yoruba: Tó bá jẹ́ òótọ́, pánẹ́ẹ̀lì náà kò ní fàyè gba òǹlò láti mú ìṣàmúlò-ètò jáde pẹ̀lú ipánípa yíyọ ààyè sí bọ́tìnì ìjáde ipá kúrò.
english: If true, the panel will not allow a user to force an application to quit by removing access to the force quit button.

yoruba: Ṣí ojú-iṣẹ́ náà gẹ́gẹ́ bíi fódàDesktop FolderDesktop Folder
Ṣí ojú-iṣẹ́ náà gẹ́gẹ́ bíi fódà
english: Open the contents of your desktop in a folder

yoruba: Parí iṣẹ́ sáà yìí láti bẹ̀rẹ̀ gẹ́gẹ́ bíi òǹlò mìíràn tàbí kí o pa kọ̀ǹpútà náà
english: Log out <UNK> of this session to log in as a different user

yoruba: Irúfẹ́ nǹkan pánẹ́ẹ̀lì yìí. Àwọn fálù tó lè jẹ́ ni "nǹkan-dúrọ́wà","nǹkan-àtòjọ-ẹ̀yàn","nǹkan-aṣàfilọ́lẹ̀","ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì bonobo","ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì-iṣẹ́"àti "àká-àtòjọ-ẹ̀yàn".
english: The type of this panel object. Possible values are "drawer-object", "menu-object", "launcher-object", "bonobo-applet", "action-applet" and "menu-bar".

yoruba: Pánẹ́ẹ̀lì ìpele-òkè tó ní nǹkan nínú
Ohun ìdánimọ̀ pánẹ́ẹ̀lì ìpele-òkè tó ní nǹkan yìí nínú.
english: The identifier of the toplevel panel which contains this object.

yoruba: Ipò nǹkan pánẹ́ẹ̀lì yìí. Oye nọ́ńbà àwọn písẹ́́ẹ̀lì tó wà láti igun pánẹ́ẹ̀lì apá òsì (tàbí òkè òòró) ni yóò sọ ipò náà ní pàtó.
english: The position of this panel object. The position is specified by the number of pixels from the left (or top if vertical) panel edge.

yoruba: Sọ ìtumọ̀ ipo ajemọ́ igun ìsàlẹ̀/ọ̀tún
english: Interpret position relative to bottom/right edge

yoruba: Tó bá jẹ́ òótọ́, a óò sọ ìtumọ̀ nǹkan náà ní àjẹmọ́ apá ọ̀tún igun pánẹ́ẹ̀lì (tàbí ìsàlẹ̀ tó bá jẹ́ òòró) náà.
english: If true, the position of the object is interpreted relative to the right (or bottom if vertical) edge of the panel.
Lock the object to the panel

yoruba: Tó bá jẹ́ òótọ́, òǹlò náà lè má gbé ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì láì jẹ́ pé ó kọ́kọ́ ṣí nǹkan tó ń lo "Má tìí" wùnrẹ̀n-àtòjọ-ẹ̀yàn.
english: If true, the user may not move the applet without first unlocking the object using the "Unlock" menuitem.

yoruba: ID ì̀pilẹ̀ Bonobo ti ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì náà - b.a "OAFIID:GNOMEClockApplet".Bọ́tìnì yìí kàn wúlò tí bọ́tìnì irúfẹ́nǹkan bá jẹ́ "ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì-bonobo".
english: The Bonobo implementation ID of the applet - e.g. "OAFIID:GNOMEClockApplet". This key is only relevant if the objecttype key is "bonobo-applet".

yoruba: Pánẹ́ẹ̀lì tí a so mọ́ dúrọ́wà
Ohun ìdánimọ̀ pánẹ́ẹ̀lì tí a somọ́ dúrọ́wà yìí. Bọ́tìnì yìí kàn wúlò tí bọ́tìnì irúfẹ́nǹkan bá jẹ́ "nǹkan-dúrọ́wà".
english: The identifier of the panel attached to this drawer. This key is only relevant if the objecttype key is "drawer-object".

yoruba: Ìtalólobó tí a ṣàfihàn fún dúrọ́wà tàbí àtòjọ-ẹ̀yàn
english: Tooltip displayed for drawer or menu

yoruba: Àyọkà tí a fẹ́ ṣàfihàn rẹ̀ nínú ìtalólobó-irinṣẹ́ fún dúrọ́wà yìí tàbí àtòjọ-ẹ̀yàn yìí. Bọ́tìnìyìí kàn wúlò tí bọ́tìnì irúfẹ́nǹkan bájẹ́"nǹkan-dúrọwà" tàbí "nǹkan-àtòjọ-ẹ̀yàn".
english: The text to display in a tooltip for this drawer or this menu. This key is only relevant if the objecttype key is "drawer-object" or "menu-object".

yoruba: Lo áíkànnù àkànṣe fún bọ́tìnì nǹkan
english: Use custom icon for object's button

yoruba: Tó bá jẹ́ òótọ́, bọ́tìnì áíkànnùàkànṣe la lò gẹ́gẹ́ bíi áíkànnù àkànṣe fún bọ́tìnì náà. Tó bajẹ́ irọ́ a óò pa bọ́tìnì áíkànnùàkànṣe tì. Bọ́tìnì yìí kàn wúlò tó bá jẹ́ bọ́tìnì irúfẹ́nǹkan jẹ́ "nǹkan-àtòjọ-ẹ̀yàn" tàbí "nǹkan-dúrọ́wà".
english: If true, the customicon key is used as a custom icon for the button. If false, the customicon key is ignored. This key is only relevant if the objecttype key is "menu-object" or "drawer-object".

yoruba: Áíkànnù tí a lò fún bọ́tìnì nǹkan

Ààyè fáìlì àwòrán tí a lò gẹ́gẹ́ bíi áíkànnù fún bọ́tìnì nǹkan náà. bọ́tìnì yìí kàn wúlò tí bọ́tìnì irúfẹ́nǹkan bá jẹ́ "nǹkan-dúrọ́wà" tàbí "nǹkan àtòjọ-ẹ̀yàn" tí bọ́tìnì áíkànnùàkànṣeìlò jẹ́ òótọ́.
english: The location of the image file used as the icon for the object's button. This key is only relevant if the objecttype key is "drawer-object" or "menu-object" and the usecustomicon key is true.

yoruba: Lo ipa àkànṣe fún àwọn àkóónú àtòjọ-ẹ̀yàn
english: Use custom path for menu contents

yoruba: Tó bá jẹ́ òótọ́, a lo bọ́tìnì ipa àtòjọ-ẹ̀yàn gẹ́gẹ́ bíi ipa ti a ti lè̀ kọ́ àwọn àkóónú àtòjọ-ẹ̀yàn.Tó bá jẹ́ irọ́, a máa pa bọ́tìnì ipaàtòjọ-ẹ̀yàn tì. Bọ́tìnì yìí kàn wúlò tí bọ́tìnì irúfẹ́nǹkan bá jẹ́ "nǹkanàtòjọ-ẹ̀yàn".
english: If true, the menupath key is used as the path from which the menu contents should be constructed. If false, the menupath key is ignored. This key is only relevant if the objecttype key is "menu-object".

yoruba: Ipa tí a ti kọ́ àwọn àkóónú àtòjọ-ẹ̀yàn. Bọ́tìnì yìí kàn wúlò tí bọ́tìnìipaàtòjọ-ẹ̀yànìlò sì jẹ́ òótọ́ tí bọ́tìnìnǹkan jẹ́"nǹkan-àtòjọ-ẹ̀yàn"
english: The path from which the menu contents is contructed. This key is only relevant if the usemenupath key is true and the objecttype key is "menu-object".

yoruba: Ààyè fáìlì ojú-iṣẹ́ tó ń ṣàpèjúwe aṣàfilọ́lẹ̀. Bọ́tìnì yìí kàn wúlò tí bọ́tìnì irúfẹ́nǹkan bá jẹ́ "nǹkan-aṣàfilọ́lẹ̀".
english: The location of the .desktop file describing the launcher. This key is only relevant if the objecttype key is "launcher-object".

yoruba: Irúfẹ́ iṣẹ́ tí bọ́tìnì yìí dúró fún. Àwọn fálù tó lè jẹ́ ni"lọ́ọ̀kì","parí iṣẹ́","rọ́ọ̀nù","wádìí"àti "ìmáwòrán". Bọ́tìnì yìí kàn wúlòtí bọ́tìnì irúfẹ́nǹkan bá jẹ́ "ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì-iṣẹ́".
english: The action type this button represents. Possible values are "lock", "logout", "run", "search" and "screenshot". This key is only relevant if the objecttype key is "action-applet".

yoruba: A gbé pánẹ́ẹ̀lì <UNK> kalẹ̀ láti ṣàfihàn lórí ojú kọ̀ǹpútà d tí kò sínílẹ̀ lọ́wọlọ́wọ́. Kò ki pánẹ́ẹ̀lì yìí.
english: Panel <UNK> is set to be displayed on screen d which is not currently available. Not loading this panel.

yoruba: Ọ̀pọ̀ àwọn àbùdá yìí lati tì sí sàlẹ̀
english: Some of these properties are locked down

yoruba: Atọ́ka árò lórí àwọn bọ́tìnì ìpamọ́
Yí àwòrán po tí pánéẹ̀lì bá wà ní òòró
english: Rotate image when panel is vertical

yoruba: Kò lè ṣí àkọsílẹ̀ tí a lò tán láìpẹ́
english: Could not open recently used document <UNK>

yoruba: Àṣìṣe àìmọ̀ wáyé nígbà tí à ń gbìyànjú láti ṣí <UNK>
english: An unknown error occurred while trying to open <UNK>.

yoruba: Pa àtòjọ Àwọn Àkọsílẹ̀ Àìpẹ́ Rẹ́?

Tí o bá pa àtòjọ Àwọn Àkọsílẹ̀ Àìpẹ́ rẹ́, wà á pa àwọn wọ̀nyí rẹ́: • Gbogbo àwọn wúnrẹ̀n láti inú Àwọn Ibìkan → wúnrẹ̀n àtòjọ-ẹ̀yàn Àwọn Àkọsílẹ̀ Àìpẹ́. • Gbogbo àwọn wúnrẹ̀n láti inú àtòjọ àwọn àkọsílẹ̀ nínú gbogbo àwọn ìṣàmúlò-ètò.
english: If you clear the Recent Documents list, you clear the following: • All items from the Places → Recent Documents menu item. • All items from the recent documents list in all applications.

yoruba: Pa gbogbo àwọn wúnrẹ̀n láti inú àtòjọ àwọn àkọsílẹ̀ àìpẹ́ rẹ́
english: Clear all items from the recent documents list

yoruba: Kò lè yí <UNK> padà láti UTF-8
Yan fáìlì láti ṣàfikún àṣẹ náà...
english: Choose a file to append to the command...

yoruba: Yan ìṣàmúlò-ètò láti wòye àpèjúwe rẹ̀.
english: Select an application to view its description.

yoruba: Àtòjọ URL tí sọ̀ kalẹ̀ lórí rọ́ọ̀nù onísọ̀rọ̀gbèsì ní ìgúnrégé tí kò tọ̀nà (d) tàbí ìgùnsí (d)
english: URI list dropped on run dialog had wrong format (d) or length (d)

yoruba: Áíkànnù àṣẹ tí a fẹ́ rọ́ọ̀nù.
english: The icon of the command to be run.

yoruba: Yan àpótí yìí láti rọ́ọ̀nù àṣẹ nínú fèrè̀̀̀̀̀̀sé támínà.
english: Select this box to run the command in a terminal window.

yoruba: Tẹ bọ́tìnì yìí láti wáròyìn fún fáìlì tí a óò ṣàfikún orúkọ rẹ̀ sí fọ́nránàṣẹ.
english: Click this button to browse for a file whose name to append to the command string.

yoruba: Fi àtòjọ àwọn ìṣàmúlò-ètò mímọ̀ hàn
Tẹ bọ́tìnì yìí láti rọ́ọ̀nù ìṣàmúlò-ètò tí a yàn tàbí àṣẹ inúààyè wúnrẹ̀n àmúwọlé àṣẹ.
english: Click this button to run the selected application or the command in the command entry field.

yoruba: Pánẹ́ẹ̀lì Igun Òkè Tí a Fẹ̀
Pánẹ́ẹ̀lì Igun Ìsàlẹ̀ Tí a Fẹ̀
Pánẹ́ẹ̀lì Igun Òsì Tí A Fẹ̀
Pánẹ́ẹ̀lì Igun Ọ̀tún Tí A Fẹ̀

Orúkọ èèyàn tí a lè kà ni èyí, tí o sì lè lò láti tọ́ka sí pánẹ́ẹ̀lì. Ìdí pàtàkì rẹ̀ ni láti ṣe iṣẹ́ gẹ́gẹ́ bíi àkọ́lé fèrèsé pánẹ́ẹ̀lì tí ó wúlò nígbà tí à ń tọpa láàrin àwọn pánẹ́ẹ̀lì.
english: This is a human readable name which you can use to identify a panel. Its main purpose is to serve as the panel's window title which is useful when navigating between panels.

yoruba: Ojú kọ̀ǹpútà X níbi tí a ti ṣàfihàn pánẹ́ẹ̀lì náà
english: X screen where the panel is displayed

yoruba: Pẹ̀lú àgbékalẹ̀-ètò ojú kọ̀ǹpútà ọlọ́pọ̀, o lè ní àwọn pánẹ́ẹ̀lì lórí ojú kọ̀ǹpútà kọ̀ọ̀kan. Bọ́tìnì yìí ń tọ́ka sí ojú kọ̀ǹpútà lọ́wọ́lọ́wọ́ tí a ti ṣàfihàn pánẹ́èlì náà.
english: With a multi-screen setup, you may have panels on each individual screen. This key identifies the current screen the panel is displayed on.

yoruba: Àpótí ìṣàfihàn Xinerama níbi tí a ti ṣàfihàn pánẹ́ẹ̀lì náà
english: Xinerama monitor where the panel is displayed

yoruba: Nínú àgbékalẹ̀-ètò Xinerama, o lè ní àwọn pánẹ́ẹ̀lì lórí àpótí ìṣàfihàn kọ̀ọ̀kan. Bọ́tìnì yìí ń tọ́ka sí àpótí ìṣàfihàn lọ́wọ́lọ́wọ́ tí a ti ṣàfihàn pánẹ́ẹ̀lì náà lé lórí.
english: In a Xinerama setup, you may have panels on each individual monitor. This key identifies the current monitor the panel is displayed on.

yoruba: Fẹ̀ẹ́ láti lè gba gbogbo ìfẹ̀sí ojú kọ̀ǹpútà
english: Expand to occupy entire screen width

yoruba: Tó bá jẹ́ òótọ́, pánẹ́ẹ̀lì náà á gba gbogbo ìfẹ̀sí ojú kọ̀ǹpútà náà (ìgasí tí o bá jẹ́ pánẹ́ẹ̀lì olóòró). Nínú móòdù yìí, pánẹ́ẹ̀lì a kàn lè gbé pánẹ́ẹ̀lì sígun ojú kọ̀ǹpútà ni. Tó bá jẹ́ irọ́, pánẹ́ẹ̀lì náà á kàn tóbi láti gba gbogbo àwọn ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì náà, àwọn aṣàfilọ́lẹ̀ àti àwọn bọ́tìnì lórí pánẹ́ẹ̀lì náà.
english: If true, the panel will occupy the entire screen width (height if this is a vertical panel). In this mode the panel can only be placed at a screen edge. If false, the panel will only be large enough to accommodate the applets, launchers and buttons on the panel.

yoruba: Ìṣàlàyé pánẹ́ẹ̀lì yìí. Àwọn fálù tó lè jẹ́ ni "òkè", "ìsàlẹ̀", "òsì", "ọ̀tún". Ní móòdù tí a fẹ̀, bọ́tìnì náà ń sọ ní pàtó igun ojú kọ̀ǹpútà tí pánẹ́ẹ̀lì náà wà lórí ẹ. Nínú móòdù tí a kò fẹ̀ ìyàtọ̀ tó wà láàrin "òkè" àti "ìsàlẹ̀" pàtàkì díẹ̀ - méjéèjì fihàn pé èyí ni pánẹ́ẹ̀lì oníbùú - ṣùgbọ́n ó ṣì ń ṣòfófói bí ó ṣe yẹ kí àwọn nǹkan pánẹ́ẹ̀lì ṣe rí Bí àpẹẹrẹ, lórí pánẹ́ẹ̀lì "òkè" bọ́tìnì àòjọ-ẹ̀yan á ta àtòjọ-ẹ̀yàn rẹ̀ sókè nísàlẹ̀ pánẹ́ẹ̀lì náà. Bẹ́ẹ̀, lórí pánẹ́ẹ̀lì "ìsàlẹ̀" a óò ta àtòjọ-ẹ̀yàn náà sókè pánẹ́ẹ̀lì náà..
english: The orientation of the panel. Possible values are "top", "bottom", "left", "right". In expanded mode the key specifies which screen edge the panel is on. In un-expanded mode the difference between "top" and "bottom" is less important - both indicate that this is a horizontal panel - but still give a useful hint as to how some panel objects should behave. For example, on a "top" panel a menu button will pop up its menu below the panel, whereas on a "bottom" panel the menu will be popped up above the panel.

yoruba: Ìgasí (ìfẹ̀sí fún pánẹ́ẹ̀lì òòró) pánẹ́ẹ̀lì náà. Pánẹ́ẹ̀lì náà ló máa sọ ní àkókò láti rọ́ọ̀nù ìwọ̀n tó kéré jù, tó sì dálé ìwọ̀n ìrísí-lẹ́tà àti àwọn atọ́ka mìíràn. A ti fi ìwọ̀n tó ga jù sí ìdá-mẹ́rin ìgasí ojú kọ̀ǹpútà (tàbí ìfẹ̀sí).
english: The height (width for a vertical panel) of the panel. The panel will determine at runtime a minimum size based on the font size and other indicators. The maximum size is fixed at one quarter of the screen height (or width).

yoruba: Ààyè pánẹ́ẹ̀lì lórí ásìsì x. Bọ́tìnì yìí kàn wúlò nínú móòdù tí a kò fẹ̀. Nínú móòdù tí a fẹ̀, ṣe ni a pa bọ́tìnì yìí tì ni, a sì gbesí igun ojú kọ̀ǹpútà tí bọ́tìnì ìṣàlàyé sọ ní pàtó
english: The location of the panel along the x-axis. This key is only relevant in un-expanded mode. In expanded mode this key is ignored and the panel is placed at the screen edge specified by the orientation key.

yoruba: Ààyè pánẹ́ẹ̀lì lórí ásìsì y. Bọ́tìnì yìí kàn wúlò nínú móòdù tí a kò fẹ̀. Nínú móòdù tí a fẹ̀, ṣe ni a pa bọ́tìnì yìí tì ni, a sì gbesí igun ojú kọ̀ǹpútà tí bọ́tìnì ìṣàlàyé sọ ní pàtó.
english: The location of the panel along the y-axis. This key is only relevant in un-expanded mode. In expanded mode this key is ignored and the panel is placed at the screen edge specified by the orientation key.

yoruba: Ààyè pánẹ́ẹ̀lì lórí ásìsì x. Bọ́tìnì yìí kàn wúlò nínú móòdù tí a kò fẹ̀. Nínú móòdù tí a fẹ̀, ṣe ni a pa bọ́tìnì yìí tì ni, a sì gbesí igun ojú kọ̀ǹpútà tí bọ́tìnì ìṣàlàyé sọ ní pàtó
english: The location of the panel along the x-axis, starting from the right of the screen. If set to -1, the value is ignored and the value of the x key is used. If the value is greater than 0, then the value of the x key is ignored. This key is only relevant in un-expanded mode. In expanded mode this key is ignored and the panel is placed at the screen edge specified by the orientation key.

yoruba: Ààyè pánẹ́ẹ̀lì lórí ásìsì y. Bọ́tìnì yìí kàn wúlò nínú móòdù tí a kò fẹ̀. Nínú móòdù tí a fẹ̀, ṣe ni a pa bọ́tìnì yìí tì ni, a sì gbesí igun ojú kọ̀ǹpútà tí bọ́tìnì ìṣàlàyé sọ ní pàtó.
english: The location of the panel along the y-axis, starting from the bottom of the screen. If set to -1, the value is ignored and the value of the y key is used. If the value is greater than 0, then the value of the y key is ignored. This key is only relevant in un-expanded mode. In expanded mode this key is ignored and the panel is placed at the screen edge specified by the orientation key.

yoruba: Tó bá jẹ́ òótọ́,a óò pa bọ́tìnì x náà tì, àá sì gbé pánẹ́ẹ̀lì náà sí àárín ásìsì x ojú kọ̀ǹpútà náà. Tí a bá ṣe ìṣòdíwọ̀n pánẹ́ẹ̀lì náà á wà nípò yẹn - tó túmọ̀ pé,pánẹ́ẹ̀lì náà á wá sókè ní àwọn ẹ̀gb́ẹ́ méjéèjì. Tó bá jẹ́ irọ́, bọ́tìnì x náà máa sọ ní pàtó ààyè pánẹ́ẹ̀lì náà.
english: If true, the x and xright keys are ignored and the panel is placed at the center of the x-axis of the screen. If the panel is resized it will remain at that position - i.e. the panel will grow on both sides. If false, the x and xright keys specify the location of the panel.

yoruba: Tó bá jẹ́ òótọ́,a óò pa bọ́tìnì y náà tì, àá sì gbé pánẹ́ẹ̀lì náà sí àárín ásìsì y ojú kọ̀ǹpútà náà. Tí a bá ṣe ìṣòdíwọ̀n pánẹ́ẹ̀lì náà á wà nípò yẹn - tó túmọ̀ pé,pánẹ́ẹ̀lì náà á wá sókè ní àwọn ẹ̀gb́ẹ́ méjéèjì. Tó bá jẹ́ irọ́, bọ́tìnì y náà máa sọ ní pàtó ààyè pánẹ́ẹ̀lì náà.
english: If true, the y and ybottom keys are ignored and the panel is placed at the center of the y-axis of the screen. If the panel is resized it will remain at that position - i.e. the panel will grow on both sides. If false, the y and ybottom keys specify the location of the panel.

yoruba: Ó fi pánẹ́ẹ̀lì pamọ́ sí igun

Tó bá jẹ́ òótọ́, a óò fi pánẹ́ẹ̀lì náà pamọ́ fún ra rẹ̀ sínú igun ojú kọ̀ǹpútà náà nígbà tí atọ́ka náà bá fi agbègbè pánẹ́ẹ̀lì náà sílẹ̀. Gbígbé atọ́ka náà lọ sí igun yẹn lẹ́ẹ̀kan si á fa kí pánẹ́ẹ̀lì náà tún farahàn.
english: If true, the panel is automatically hidden into a corner of the screen when the pointer leaves the panel area. Moving the pointer to that corner again will cause the panel to re-appear.

yoruba: Tó bá jẹ́ òótọ́, ìfipamọ́ àti àìfipamọ́ pánẹ́ẹ̀lì yìí á jẹ́ ìṣàfarawé kọ̀ǹpútà. ní èyí tí kò bá fi ṣẹlẹ̀ lẹ́sẹ̀kẹsẹ̀.
english: If true, hiding and un-hiding of this panel will be animated rather than happening instantly.

yoruba: Tó bá jẹ́ ò̀ótọ́,a óò gbé àwọn bọ́tìnì sí ẹ̀̀̀gbẹ́ pánẹ́ẹ̀lì kọ̀ọ̀kan tí a lè lò láti gbé pánẹ́ẹ̀lìnáà lọ sí igun ojú kọ̀ǹpútà náà. Yóò sì fi bọ́tìnì kan tó ń ṣàfihàn sílẹ̀
english: If true, buttons will be placed on each side of the panel which may be used to move the panel to edge of the screen, leaving only a button showing.

yoruba: Fún àwon atọ́ka-árò lágbára lórí àwọn bọ́tìnì ìpamọ́
Tó bá jẹ́ ò̀ótọ́,a óò gbé àwọn atọ́ka-árò sórí àwọn bọ́tìnì ìpamọ́. Bọ́tìnì yìíkàn wúlò tí àwọn bọ́tìnìtí a fún lágbára bá jẹ́ òótọ́.
english: If true, arrows will be placed on the hide buttons. This key is only relevant if the enablebuttons key is true.

yoruba: Ń sọ ní pàtó oye ìdádúró ọ̀kẹ́-ìṣísẹ̀ lẹ́yìn tí atọ́ka náà ti jáde lágbègbè náà kí pánẹ́ẹ̀lì tó di pípamọ́. Ìgbà tí bọ́tìnì ìpamọ́aládàáṣe bá jẹ́ òótọ́ nìkan ni bọ́tìnì yìí wúlò.
english: Specifies the number of milliseconds delay after the pointer leaves the panel area before the panel is automatically hidden. This key is only relevant if the autohide key is true.

yoruba: Ń sọ ní pàtó oye ìdádúró ọ̀kẹ́-ìṣísẹ̀ lẹ́yìn tí atọ́ka náà ti wọ agbègbè náà kí pánẹ́ẹ̀lì tó dá farahàn. Ìgbà tí bọ́tìnì ìpamọ́aládàáṣe bá jẹ́ òótọ́ nìkan ni bọ́tìnì yìí wúlò.
english: Specifies the number of milliseconds delay after the pointer enters the panel area before the panel is automatically re-shown. This key is only relevant if the autohide key is true.

yoruba: Àwọn písẹ́ẹ̀lì ta lè rí nígbà ìpamọ́
Ń sọ ní pàtó iye àwọn písẹ́ẹ̀lì tó fojúhàn nígbà tí a fi páńẹ̀ẹlì náà pamọ́ sí igun kan. Bọ́tìnì yìí kàn wúlò tí bọ́tìnì ìpamọ́aládàáṣe bá jẹ́ òótọ́.
english: Specifies the number of pixels visible when the panel is automatically hidden into a corner. This key is only relevant if the autohide key is true.

yoruba: Ìyárasí tó yẹ kí àwọn ìṣàfarawé kọ̀ǹpútà ó ti yọ. Àwọn fálù tó lè jẹ́ ni "falẹ̀", "àárín" àti "ìyára". Bọ́tìnì yìí kàn wúlò tí bọ́tìnì àwọn mú ìṣàfarawé kọ̀ǹpútàṣiṣẹ́ bá jẹ́ òótọ́.
english: The speed in which panel animations should occur. Possible values are "slow", "medium" and "fast". This key is only relevant if the enableanimations key is true.

yoruba: Irúfẹ́ ẹ̀yìn wo la ó lò fún pánẹ́ẹ̀lì yìí. Àwọn fálù tó lè jẹ́ ni "gtk" - a óò lo ẹ̀yìn wíjẹ́ẹ̀tì ìpéwọ̀n GTK+, "àwọ̀" a óò lo bọ́tìnì àwọ̀ gẹ́gẹ́ bíi àwọ̀ ẹ̀yìn tàbí "àwòrán" - àwòrán tí bọ́tìnì àwòrán sọ la ó lò gẹ́gẹ́ bíi ẹ̀yìn.
english: Which type of background should be used for this panel. Possible values are "gtk" - the default GTK+ widget background will be used, "color" - the color key will be used as background color or "image" - the image specified by the image key will be used as background.

yoruba: Ń sọ níp pàtó àwọ̀ ẹ̀yìn fún pánẹ́ẹ̀lì inú ìgúnrégé #RGB.
english: Specifies the background color for the panel in #RGB format.

yoruba: Ń sọ ní pàtó dídí ìgúnrégé àwọ̀ ẹ̀yìn . Tí àwọ̀ náà kò bá dí pátá (fálù tó kéré sí 65535) a óò to àwọ̀ náà pọ̀ sórí àwòrán ẹ̀yìn ojú-iṣẹ́.
english: Specifies the opacity of the background color format. If the color is not completely opaque (a value of less than 65535), the color will be composited onto the desktop background image.

yoruba: Ń sọ fáìlì tí a óò lò ní pàtó fún ẹ̀yìn àwòrán. Tí àwòrán náà bá ní ṣánẹ́ẹ̀lì alpha a óò tòójọ sórí àwòrán ẹ̀yìn ojú-iṣẹ́.
english: Specifies the file to be used for the background image. If the image contains an alpha channel it will be composited onto the desktop background image.

yoruba: Tó bá jẹ́ òótọ́, a óò ṣe ìgbéléwọ̀n àwòrán (
english: If true, the image will be scaled (retaining the aspect ratio of the image) to the panel height (if horizontal).

yoruba: Tí ó bá jẹ́ òótọ́, a óò gbé àwòrán léwọ̀n àwọn ojúùwọ̀n pánẹ́ẹ̀lì. Réṣíò aspect àwòrán áwà bó ṣe wà.
english: If true, the image will be scaled to the panel dimensions. The aspect ratio of the image will not be maintained.

yoruba: Yí àwòrán po lórí àwọn pánẹ́ẹ̀lì òòró
Tó bá jẹ́ òótọ́, a óò yí àwòrán ẹ̀yìn po tí pánẹ́ẹ̀lì náà bá jẹ́ olóòró.
english: If true, the background image will be rotated when the panel is oriented vertically.

yoruba: Nígbà tí a bá ti pa dórọ́wà jẹ, àti dúrọ́wà àti àwọn ààtò rẹ̀ máa sọnù.
english: When a drawer is deleted, the drawer and its settings are lost.

yoruba: Nígbà tí a bá ti pa pánẹ́ẹ̀lì jẹ, àti pánẹ́ẹ̀lì àti àwọn ààtò rẹ̀ máa sọnù.
english: When a panel is deleted, the panel and its settings are lost.

yoruba: Ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì alábọ̀dé kan fún ìyẹ̀wò pánẹ́ẹ̀lì GNOME-2.0
english: A simple applet for testing the GNOME-2.0 panel

yoruba: Sọ ní pàtó IID ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì tí a fẹ́ kì
english: Specify an applet IID to load

yoruba: Sọ ní pàtó ààyè gconf tí a fẹ́ fi àwọn ìkúndùn ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì pamọ́ sí
english: Specify a gconf location in which the applet preferences should be stored

yoruba: Sọ́ ní pàtó ìwọ̀n ápúlẹ́ẹ̀̀tì gan níbẹ̀rẹ̀ (kékeré, àárín, ńlá-púpọ̀ abbl.)
english: Specify the initial size of the applet (xx-small, medium, large etc.)

yoruba: Sọ ní pàtó ìṣàlàyé ìbẹ̀rẹ̀ ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì (òkè, ìsàlẹ̀, òsì tàbí ọ̀tún)Size
english: Specify the initial orientation of the applet (top, bottom, left or right)

yoruba: Ìlò bọ́tìnì yìí nínú GNOME 2.6 ti kúrò láṣà.fún 'ìgúnrégé' bọ́tìnì. A tọ́jú ìtọsẹ̀ náà fún ìbámu pẹ̀lú àwọn ẹ̀yà tó ti pẹ́.
english: The use of this key was deprecated in GNOME 2.28 in favour of the use of timezones. The schema is retained for compatibility with older versions.

yoruba: Ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì tó ní ìṣàlàyé pánẹ́ẹ̀lì nínú
Sọ ní pàtó ìṣàlàyé ìbẹ̀rẹ̀ ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì (òkè, ìsàlẹ̀, òsì tàbí ọ̀tún)Orientation
english: Specify the initial orientation of the applet (top, bottom, left or right)

yoruba: Irúfẹ́ nǹkan pánẹ́ẹ̀lì yìí. Àwọn fálù tó lè jẹ́ ni "nǹkan-dúrọ́wà","nǹkan-àtòjọ-ẹ̀yàn","nǹkan-aṣàfilọ́lẹ̀","ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì bonobo","ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì-iṣẹ́"àti "àká-àtòjọ-ẹ̀yàn".
english: The type of this panel object. Possible values are "drawer-object", "menu-object", "launcher-object", "external-applet", "action-applet", "menu-bar" and "separator".

yoruba: ID ì̀pilẹ̀ Bonobo ti ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì náà - b.a "OAFIID:GNOMEClockApplet".Bọ́tìnì yìí kàn wúlò tí bọ́tìnì irúfẹ́nǹkan bá jẹ́ "ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì-bonobo".
english: This key is deprecated, following the migration to a new library for applets. The Bonobo implementation ID of the applet - e.g. "OAFIID:GNOMEClockApplet". This key is only relevant if the objecttype key is "bonobo-applet".

yoruba: ID ì̀pilẹ̀ Bonobo ti ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì náà - b.a "OAFIID:GNOMEClockApplet".Bọ́tìnì yìí kàn wúlò tí bọ́tìnì irúfẹ́nǹkan bá jẹ́ "ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì-bonobo".
english: The implementation ID of the applet - e.g. "ClockAppletFactory::ClockApplet". This key is only relevant if the objecttype key is "external-applet" (or the deprecated "bonobo-applet").
Failed to open the time settings

yoruba: Ìgúnrégéàkànṣe:state" or "province" should use that instead of "region
Fátìrì fún ìṣẹ̀dá àwọn ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì aago.

Àtòjọ àwọn ID ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì pánẹ́ẹ̀lì. ID kọ̀ọ̀kan ń tọ́ka sí nǹkan pánẹ́ẹ̀lì kọ̀ọ̀kan (b.a.aṣàfilọ́lẹ̀, bọ́tìnì iṣẹ́ tàbí àká/bọ́tìnì àtòjọ-ẹ̀yàn). A fi àwọn ààtò fún àwọn nǹkankọ̀ọ̀kan pamọ́ sínú /apps/panel/objects/$(id).
english: A list of panel object IDs. Each ID identifies an individual panel object (e.g. an applet, launcher, action button or menu button/bar). The settings for each of these objects are stored in /apps/panel/objects/$(id).

yoruba: Mú àtòjọ àtòjọ-ètò inú onísọ̀rọ̀gbèsì "Rọ́ọ̀nù Ìsàmúlò-ètò" ṣíṣẹ
Mú ìkádìí-aládàáṣe nínú onísọ̀rọ̀gbèsì "Rọ́ọ̀nù Ìṣàmúlò-ètò" ṣiṣẹ́
english: The list of commands used in the past in the "Run Application" dialog.

yoruba: Ìtalólobó tí a ṣàfihàn fún dúrọ́wà tàbí àtòjọ-ẹ̀yàn
Áíkànnù tí a lò fún bọ́tìnì nǹkan

Ààyè fáìlì àwòrán tí a lò gẹ́gẹ́ bíi áíkànnù fún bọ́tìnì nǹkan náà. bọ́tìnì yìí kàn wúlò tí bọ́tìnì irúfẹ́nǹkan bá jẹ́ "nǹkan-dúrọ́wà" tàbí "nǹkan àtòjọ-ẹ̀yàn" tí bọ́tìnì áíkànnùàkànṣeìlò jẹ́ òótọ́.
english: The location of the image file used as the icon for the object's button. If empty, the default icon for the menu will be used.

yoruba: Ipa tí a ti kọ́ àwọn àkóónú àtòjọ-ẹ̀yàn. Bọ́tìnì yìí kàn wúlò tí bọ́tìnìipaàtòjọ-ẹ̀yànìlò sì jẹ́ òótọ́ tí bọ́tìnìnǹkan jẹ́"nǹkan-àtòjọ-ẹ̀yàn"
english: The path from which the menu contents is contructed. If empty, the menu will be the default applications menu.

yoruba: Tó bá jẹ́ òótọ́, a óò sọ ìtumọ̀ nǹkan náà ní àjẹmọ́ apá ọ̀tún igun pánẹ́ẹ̀lì (tàbí ìsàlẹ̀ tó bá jẹ́ òòró) náà.
english: If set to 'end', the position of the object is interpreted relative to the right (or bottom if vertical) edge of the panel.

yoruba: Irúfẹ́ ẹ̀yìn wo la ó lò fún pánẹ́ẹ̀lì yìí. Àwọn fálù tó lè jẹ́ ni "gtk" - a óò lo ẹ̀yìn wíjẹ́ẹ̀tì ìpéwọ̀n GTK+, "àwọ̀" a óò lo bọ́tìnì àwọ̀ gẹ́gẹ́ bíi àwọ̀ ẹ̀yìn tàbí "àwòrán" - àwòrán tí bọ́tìnì àwòrán sọ la ó lò gẹ́gẹ́ bíi ẹ̀yìn.
english: Which type of background should be used for this panel. Possible values are "none" - the default GTK+ widget background will be used, "color" - the color key will be used as background color or "image" - the image specified by the image key will be used as background.

yoruba: A kò ṣègbékalẹ̀ bọ́tìnì <UNK>, kò lè ki aṣàfilọ̀lẹ̀
english: Launcher location is not set, cannot load launcher

yoruba: Fátìrì fún ìṣẹ̀dá àwọn ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì aago.
Ápúlẹ́ẹ̀tì alábọ̀dé kan fún ìyẹ̀wò pánẹ́ẹ̀lì GNOME-2.0
english: A simple applet for testing the GNOME panel

yoruba: Ṣí ojú-iṣẹ́ náà gẹ́gẹ́ bíi fódà
Àṣẹ fún ìbẹ̀rẹ̀ kò lè jẹ́ òfìfo
english: The startup command cannot be empty

yoruba: Àṣẹ fún ìbẹ̀rẹ̀ kò lè jẹ́ òfìfo
english: The startup command is not valid

yoruba: Fi ojú kọ̀ǹpútà píláàṣì hàn tí sáà náà bá ti bẹ̀rẹ̀
english: Show the splash screen when the session starts up

yoruba: Tí a bá fún lágbára sáà-gnome á dáfi sáà náà pamọ́. Láì jẹ́ bẹ́ẹ̀, onísọ̀rọ̀gbèsì ìparí iṣẹ́ á ní ẹ̀yàn láti fi sáà náà pamọ́.
english: If enabled, gnome-session will save the session automatically. Otherwise, the logout dialog will have an option to save the session.

yoruba: Tí a bá fún lágbára iṣẹ́ sáà gnome á́ ṣí òǹlò náà lórí kó tó parí sáà kan.
english: If enabled, gnome-session will prompt the user before ending a session.

yoruba: Àwòrán tí a fẹ́ láti lò fún ojú kọ̀ǹpútà píláàṣì
english: Preferred Image to use for login splash screen

yoruba: Fálù tó jẹmọ́ ipa tó dálé atọ́nà $datadir/pixmaps/ ni èyí. Àwọn ẹ̀ka-atọ́nà àti àwọn orúkọ àwòrán jẹ́ àwọn fálù tó fẹsẹ̀múlẹ̀. Ìyípadà fálù yìí á kan ìbẹ̀rẹ̀ iṣẹ́ sáà tókàn.
english: This is a relative path value based off the $datadir/pixmaps/ directory. Sub-directories and image names are valid values. Changing this value will effect the next session login.

yoruba: Ètò tí a ti bẹ̀rẹ̀ àwọn ì̀ṣàmúlò-ètò nínú sáà náà.
english: List of applications that are part of the default session.

Ó kùnà láti ṣí ìṣàfihàn Ètò Fèrèsé X <UNK>
english: Failed to open X Window System display <UNK>

yoruba: Ó sọ ìdarapọ̀ nù fún ìsàfihàn <UNK>; Ó ṣeé ṣe kí a pa sáfà X tàbí o pa/ba alábòójútó fèrèsé náà jẹ́.
english: Lost connection to the display <UNK>; most likely the X server was shut down or you killed/destroyed the window manager.

yoruba: Àṣìṣe IO ńlá d (<UNK>) lórí ìṣàfihàn <UNK>.
english: Fatal IO error d (<UNK>) on display <UNK>.

english: Some other program is already using the key <UNK> with modifiers x as a binding

yoruba: A kò tíì soríkì àṣe d kankan.
english: No command d has been defined.

yoruba: Aṣẹ̀dá-ìtọ́ka bọ́tìnì náà máa ń ti àtòjọ-ẹ̀yàn fèrèsé́ . Ìgúnrégé náà jọ "lt;Ìdarígt;a" tàbí "lt;Shiftgt;lt;Altgt;F1". Pásà náà fanimọ́ra, ó sì ń fàyè gba lẹ́tà kékeré àti gòdògbò àti àwọn ìgékúrú bí i "lt;Ctlgt;" àti "lt;Ctrlgt;". Tí o bá gbé ẹ̀yàn náà kalẹ̀ sí fọ́nrán àkànṣe "kò ní agbára mọ́", a jẹ́ pé kò ní sí aṣẹ̀dá-ìtọ́ka bọ́tìnì fún iṣẹ́ yìí nìyẹn.
english: The format looks like "<Control>a" or "<Shift><Alt>F1". The parser is fairly liberal and allows lower or upper case, and also abbreviations such as "<Ctl>" and "<Ctrl>". If you set the option to the special string "disabled", then there will be no keybinding for this action.

yoruba: Aṣẹ̀dá-ìtọ́ka bọ́tìnì náà máa ń ti àtòjọ-ẹ̀yàn fèrèsé́ . Ìgúnrégé náà jọ "lt;Ìdarígt;a" tàbí "lt;Shiftgt;lt;Altgt;F1". Pásà náà fanimọ́ra, ó sì ń fàyè gba lẹ́tà kékeré àti gòdògbò àti àwọn ìgékúrú bí i "lt;Ctlgt;" àti "lt;Ctrlgt;". Tí o bá gbé ẹ̀yàn náà kalẹ̀ sí fọ́nrán àkànṣe "kò ní agbára mọ́", a jẹ́ pé kò ní sí aṣẹ̀dá-ìtọ́ka bọ́tìnì fún iṣẹ́ yìí nìyẹn.
english: The format looks like "<Control>a" or "<Shift><Alt>F1". The parser is fairly liberal and allows lower or upper case, and also abbreviations such as "<Ctl>" and "<Ctrl>". If you set the option to the special string "disabled", then there will be no keybinding for this action. This keybinding may be reversed by holding down the "shift" key; therefore, "shift" cannot be one of the keys it uses.
